  "prompt": "What is the best interview questions asked by you ?",
  "response": "As an AI, I don't conduct interviews myself, but I can suggest some insightful interview questions that can help evaluate a candidate's skills, experience, and cultural fit. Here are some examples:\n\n**Technical/Role-Specific Questions:**\n1. Can you walk me through a recent project you worked on? What were your responsibilities, and what challenges did you face?\n2. How do you stay updated with the latest trends and technologies in your field?\n3. Describe a time when you had to learn a new technology or tool quickly. How did you approach it?\n\n**Behavioral Questions:**\n4. Tell me about a time when you worked as part of a team. What role did you play, and how did you contribute to the team's success?\n5. Describe a situation where you had to handle a difficult colleague or client. How did you manage the conflict?\n6. Give an example of a goal you set and achieved. How did you plan and execute it?\n\n**Problem-Solving Questions:**\n7. Can you describe a complex problem you solved and the steps you took to resolve it?\n8. How do you prioritize tasks when you have multiple deadlines to meet?\n9. Tell me about a time when you had to make a decision with incomplete information. What was the outcome?\n\n**Cultural Fit Questions:**\n10. What type of work environment do you thrive in?\n11. How do you handle stress and pressure?\n12. What motivates you in your career?\n\n**Self-Reflection Questions:**\n13. What are your greatest strengths and weaknesses?\n14. Where do you see yourself in five years?\n15. Can you give an example of a mistake you made and what you learned from it?\n\nThese questions are designed to elicit detailed responses that provide insight into the candidate's abilities, experiences, and personality, helping interviewers make informed hiring decisions.",
